node.title: Two light earthquakes rattle North Island's East Coast on Christmas Day
node.description: They happened in the early hours of the morning.
node.content: ["Two light earthquakes have rattled the East Coast of the North Island on Saturday morning.\n", "At 5:03am, GeoNet recorded a 3.5-magnitude quake, 5km northeast of Ruatoria at 16 kilometres deep.", "GeoNet said it was followed by a 4-magnitude jolt shortly after at 5:57am, at 30km deep and 5km west of Te Araroa.", "RNZ"]
